create a simple unit test&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13041021" author="koven2049" created="Mon, 30 May 2011 06:47:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for stack&apos;s comments.&lt;br/&gt;
I added a simple unit test and fix some bugs.&lt;br/&gt;
This patch only support &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0-9,A-Z,a-z&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; by the variable &quot;sascii&quot;. Is it necessary to add some other charactors? Or allows users to customize?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
